assets.name: assets/5uBg4Bq9tSY
assets.description:
USS Rana 9 had been travelling thousand years transporting human remains from earth to the stars when the accident happened and the main shield failed.  

Once the massive bow of the ship collased due to stress, it caused space debris to sweep through the 3 kilometer length of the ship at enormous speeds. This destroyed eventually most of the citys apartment blocks and civic buildings and other superstructure from inside to space. 

Now after another thousand years only few structures remain of the once great last city of mankind. All roads, green areas and lakes seem to have been swept to space eventually. 

It can be noted how even the massive water reservoir which was shielded by diamond cell has shattered and water leaked inside. The bullet trains that once moved citizens around have also vanished - only one husk remains floating around, probably grave to many people

The artificial sun that was also the ships hydrogen power source still seems to operate - at least partly

Mysteriously some structures still seem to have electricity and lights, almost like someone was still alive after a millenia..

Experimenting modelling a chest in an efficient manner. Here I subdivided a cube and extruded pectoral muscles, then merged the verices at the top and created a dip at the base to ger a feeling of the ribcage's shape.

Still need to work on doing better hips.

But generally happy with this version of Lord Arbourshade; who should present themselves as a well toned dexterity fighter.

assets.name: assets/cmmPrXHEhLG
assets.description:
Concept of the "Grace" in the 3rd dimension -from Terry Goodkind's series of books, The Sword of Truth.

The original picture you can find here: http://vignette3.wikia.nocookie.net/sot/images/c/c0/Grace2.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20100323011505

From the text, "Though a Grace appears simple, it represents the whole of everything. The outer circle represents the beginning of the underworld -the infinite world of the dead. Out beyond the circle, the underworld, there is nothing else; there is only forever. The square represents the Veil, separating the world of the dead, from the world of the living (the inner circle). The star at the center of it all is the light -the Creator, with rays of His gift of magic coming from the light to pass through all the boundaries... 

The Grace is the depiction of the continuum of the Gift."
